Where your thinking becomes interesting is when you talk about forces pushing something away from equilibrium and returning it to center.

That’s a classic concept in physics called an attractor.

Examples:
	•	a pendulum returning to rest
	•	a marble settling in a bowl
	•	ecosystems stabilizing around equilibrium
	•	neural networks converging during training

The system has a stable state and perturbations push it away temporarily.

