3. Your magnet thought experiment

The idea of four magnets around a floating object is actually very similar to real physics experiments.

But there’s an important catch.

Earnshaw’s theorem says:

You cannot stably levitate a magnet using only static magnetic fields.

So if you tried four permanent magnets arranged north/south/east/west, the center point would actually be unstable.

The object would drift away.

Stable magnetic levitation requires something like:
	•	diamagnetic materials
	•	superconductors
	•	active feedback control
	•	spinning gyroscopes

